OL,3,CMore than 300 police officers and
OL,4,Cstaff declare Freemasons involvement
OL,6,FThis meant officers and staff were
OL,7,Frequired to declare membership "past
OL,8,For present" of any organisation that
OL,9,Fis "hierarchical, has confidential
OL,10,Fmembership and requires members to
OL,11,Fsupport and protect each other".
OL,13,FThe move prompted the bodies
OL,14,Frepresenting Freemasons in England,
OL,15,FWales, the Isle of Man and the Channel
OL,16,FIslands to begin legal action over the
OL,17,Fforce's decision at the High Court,
OL,18,Fwith the organisations claiming that
OL,19,Fthe move is discriminatory against
OL,20,FFreemasons.
